&lt;p&gt;Hi Fred,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;TensorFlow doesn&#39;t provide any benefit in the acceleration here, in fact it is below optimal as it doesn&#39;t use multiple CUDA streams.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;We chose TensorFlow for convenience as it provides most of the functionality we need (activation layers, multithreading, queues). More importantly, we wanted to build something others would be familiar with already (Python + TensorFlow) rather than creating something from scratch and TensorFlow is a good balance between performance and usability.&lt;/div&gt;

